.TH "xemaclite_set_mac_address" 9 "xemaclite_set_mac_address" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xemaclite_set_mac_address \- Set the MAC address for this device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xemaclite_set_mac_address
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "void *address "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Pointer to the network device instance
.IP "address" 12
Void pointer to the sockaddr structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function copies the HW address from the sockaddr strucutre to the
net_device structure and updates the address in HW.
.SH "RETURN"
Error if the net device is busy or 0 if the addr is set
successfully
